place.name: BODHAM
place.gazetteerText: BODHAM, a parish in Erpingham district, Norfolk; 3 miles E of Holt, 5¼ W of the line of the projected railway to Cromer, and 12 E of Walsingham r. station. Post Town, Holt, under Thetford. Acres, 1, 688. Real property, £2,007. Pop., 316. Houses, 74. The property is divided among a few. The living is a rectory in the diocese of Norwich. Value not reported. Patron, T. J. Mott, Esq. The church is very good. (In 1870-72, John Marius Wilson's Imperial Gazetteer of England and Wales)
